            {
              "pointer": "2",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "LINAC"
                ],
                "institute": "1CANSAS"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Experiment performed using electron",
                "linac at the Saskatchewan Accelerator Laboratory (SAL)",
                "and linac at the University of Illinois. Both",
                "experimental facilities - linacs as well as photon",
                "taggers were almost identical."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The scattering target of distilled water was",
                "contained in a thin-walled Lucite box, 7.6 cm thick,",
                "with 0.13 mm Mylar entrance and exit windows for the",
                "incident beam."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The photon detectors were two large",
                "cylindrical NaI(Tl) detectors placed at 45deg and",
                "135deg with respect to the photon beam axis. For the",
                "energy range 89-108 MeV, data were also taken with the",
                "detectors at 90deg. Each detector subtended a solid",
                "angle of about 0.05 sr and was surrounded by both",
                "passive and active shielding."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "TAGD"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " High duty factor beams of electrons were",
                "incident on a thin aluminum radiator.",
                "Momentum-analyzed residual electrons were detected in",
                "a multi- element hodoscope of plastic scintillators.",
                "Coincidence between scattered photons and tagging",
                "electrons was required.The Illinois experiment covered",
                "the tagged photon energy range 27-64 MeV. The SAL",
                "experiment covered the range 60-108 MeV"
              ]
            }
          ],
